formThreeIdData.physicalProgressReason: 1.	The variation of expenditure certified to be incurred by Architect and Engineer and expenditure incurred and paid certified by Chartered Accountant is bound to be there as physical progress of project is always at different level then reporting of invoices and expenses bills in financial accounts as they are accounted and when received.  Further the project is complete as per certificate given by Architect and variation in expenses incurred on construction and interest is explained as per notes to certificate. Subject to that, there is coherence between progress of project as well as incurrence and payment of expenses considering project specification.
formThreeIdData.notesToCertificate:
1.	Un-booked inventory valuation is arrived on the basis of estimated Jantri/ Circle rates applied to projected construction area as represented by Builder and also on the basis of booked units on similar floor.
2.	We hereby certify actual cost incurred and paid by Applicant Builder verified on the basis of books of account submitted before us and on the basis of explanation and information given to us during the course of verification.
3.	Balance receivable from booked units is stated on the basis of agreed amount between both parties and also on the basis of sale deed already entered into for units on similar floor.
4.	The project is coming up on land owned by partners in their personal capacity and Land development agreement has been entered into. Therefore no actual cost of land is payable. Estimate of land cost is derived on the basis of Jantri/circle rate prevailing as informed by promoter. Proceeds of land sale will be paid to land owners as and when unit is sold and same will be shown as incurred cost of land in RERA Certificate.
5.	As represented by developers, there is huge increase of cost of construction during the last 3 years since the start of project. This has resulted in undue and unexpected increase of actual cost of construction compare to estimated cost of construction.  There  is also  corresponding increase in sale price of units.
6.	Estimate of projected cost of construction has increased considerably from what was given at the time of RERA registration due to subsequent increase in price of construction materials and other cost without any revision in plan and therefore actual cost incurred and paid which is auto-reflected in form 3 column a(ii)  is not correct. Estimated cost of construction is expected to be higher by Rs. 3,36,60,680/- to the extent of total construction cost Rs. 11,16,69,366/- as represented by Promoter and certificate of Architect has been obtained in this behalf.  As on date actual construction expenses is Rs. 10,96,89,748/- as against above estimate.
7.	As a result of escalation in cost of project by Rs. 3,36,60,680/-, withdrawal limit as shown in column 8 of form 3 is shown negative. If estimated construction cost is revised to Rs. 11,16,69,366/-, the withdrawal limit would be Rs. 56,99,871/- (Rs. 14,04,31,018  Rs. 13,47,31,147) which is correct as per books of accounts and based on actual expenditure incurred and paid. 
8.	Certain amounts of booking were deposited in other then RERA bank a/c. therefore actual withdrawals from separate account as reported in column 7 above, Rs. 13,47,31,147/- is not accurate because, we are unable to ascertain whether amount was withdrawn for project or not.
9.	During the year, amount of Rs. 208,49,506/- was deposited in NON- RERA  bank account  instead of RERA Account which is not correct. Promoter has represented that he was under impression that as project had obtained BU permission, he was permitted to do so.
